🚀 PM2 ONLY — FULL PRACTICAL GUIDE

Your flow now:

Frontend (5173)
   ↓
Backend PM2 (5000)
   ↓
8 Node Workers
🔥 1. Start Server

Go to backend folder:

cd D:\Node_js\Ecommerce\ecommerce-backend

Run:

pm2 start app.js -i max --name sahimoncart
🔍 Meaning
app.js = your server file
-i max = use all CPU cores
--name sahimoncart = custom process name
🔥 2. See Running Servers
pm2 list

You’ll see:

id | name         | mode    | status
0  | sahimoncart  | cluster | online
1  | sahimoncart  | cluster | online
...
🔥 3. Stop Server
pm2 stop sahimoncart
🔥 4. Restart Server
pm2 restart sahimoncart
🔥 5. Delete Server

(remove from PM2 list)

pm2 delete sahimoncart
🔥 6. See Logs

Live logs:

pm2 logs sahimoncart
Only errors:
pm2 logs sahimoncart --err
🔥 7. Monitor CPU / RAM
pm2 monit

Shows:

CPU usage
Memory
Workers
Live stats
🔥 8. Test Load Balancing

Since PM2 cluster uses same port:

http://localhost:5000

Workers share port internally.

Add test route in app.js
app.get("/test", (req, res) => {
  res.json({
    pid: process.pid,
    port: PORT
  });
});
Test in browser console:
fetch("/api/test")
  .then(res => res.json())
  .then(console.log);

OR direct:

http://localhost:5000/test

Run many times.

Expected:
pid changes every request

Example:

{ pid: 1120 }
{ pid: 3340 }
{ pid: 2288 }

👉 That means PM2 load balancing works.

🔥 9. Scale Workers Manually

Use specific count:

pm2 start app.js -i 4 --name sahimoncart

Use only 4 workers.

🔥 10. Increase / Decrease Later
pm2 scale sahimoncart 6

Now 6 workers.

🔥 11. Auto Start on PC Restart
pm2 save
pm2 startup
🔥 12. Reload Without Downtime

Best for updates:

pm2 reload sahimoncart

No downtime restart.

🔥 13. Frontend Connection

In Vite config proxy, target:

target: "http://localhost:5000"

Because PM2 serves on 5000.

